yesterday, was unlikely to have been fully subscribed. The bank will detail
the size of the shortfall before trading opens in Australia today.
CS First Boston plans to exercise its right, expressed in the underwriting
agreement, to seek tenders for subscriptions to outstanding entitlements at
the issue price of ADollars 3 a share. Any remaining shares will be taken up
by CS First Boston or sub-underwriters.
Westpac has also launched a USDollars 350m debenture offering in the United
States. Underwritten by First Boston Corporation and Merrill Lynch, the
issue is priced to yield 7.982 per cent.
AMP Society has reduced its stake in National Australia Bank to 6.95 per
cent from 8.08 per cent. AMP is Westpac's largest shareholder, with a 15 per
cent interest, and also controls just under 7 per cent of ANZ Banking Group.
