<TEXT>
VARDON, the leisure attractions group which owns the London and York
Dungeons, has agreed to buy Sea Life Centres for Pounds 9.9m in cash and
stock, and plans a share placement, and Stock Exchange listing, to help fund
the acquisition.
Sea Life owns and operates eight marine life centres around Britain and
operates the Blackpool Centre, in which it has a 50 per cent stake with
First Leisure.
Vardon acquired the Dungeons in March for Pounds 5.6m from Kunick after Mr
