dividend of 0.25p.
Vardon is forecasting pre-tax profits of Pounds 2.3m, earnings per share of
4p, and a final dividend of 0.5p per share for the year.
Under the terms of the deal the Pounds 9.9m purchase price will be satisfied
by Pounds 2.5m cash and the issue of 16.36m Vardon shares, of which 11.9m
will be placed on behalf of the vendors at 45p per share.
The cash element of the purchase, together with about Pounds 1.3m of working
capital for the group, will be provided through the placement of a further
11m shares in Vardon at the same price.
