described the group's past accounting practices as 'sharp' and 'at the
cutting edge'; he said the board was looking critically at practices
previously employed, such as the capitalisation of interest, fair value
accounting, the charging of consultancy fees to acquisition targets, and the
capitalisation of acquisition costs.
