FT  24 SEP 92 / Building orders show fall on year
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By ANDREW TAYLOR, Construction Correspondent
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
THE RECESSION in the construction industry is tightening rather than
slackening its grip, according to government figures published yesterday.
The Environment Department said that construction orders won by British
contractors fell 16 per cent during the three months to the end of July
compared with the corresponding period last year.
Private-sector orders by industry and commerce were among the worst
affected.
Private industrial orders were 26 per cent lower than in the corresponding
period a year before, while private commercial orders, mainly for offices
and shops, were 22 per cent lower.
Private housing orders on the same basis were 15 per cent lower. However,
public housing orders, including those from housing associations, were 24
per cent higher than in the corresponding period.
