FT  24 SEP 92 / Rural jobs gloom
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
MORE THAN 150,000 rural jobs may be lost in the 1990s as a result of a
contraction in agriculture and industries that depend on farming, the Rural
Development Commission said yesterday. It added that an estimated 14,000
families were homeless in rural areas and that homelessness was growing
faster there than in towns.
