<TEXT>
CHILE plans to keep its budget in surplus next year, despite an impending
election, Mr Alejandro Foxley, finance minister, said yesterday, George
Graham writes in Washington.
He told an audience of bankers and investors at the International Monetary
Fund and the World Bank annual meetings in Washington the annual budget
would show a surplus for the fourth year in a row. Chile's economic growth
