<HEADLINE>
FT  23 SEP 92 / Commodities and Agriculture: Jet fuel futures approved
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By BARBARA HARRISON
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Applications to trade futures contracts on jet fuel and world cotton were
approved yesterday by the Commodity Futures Trading Commission, the US
futures industry regulator.
The jet fuel contract will be traded at the New York Commodity Exchange
(COMEX), which plans to launch the product in early 1993. The contract will
be for physical delivery of 1,000 barrels of fungible aviation kerosene,
Colonial Grade 51 to the US Gulf coast.
Until now, only the New York Mercantile Exchange had offered US energy
futures. Nymex is the biggest marketplace for such products. Comex boasts
the world's largest market in gold and silver futures.
The world cotton contract will begin trading October 1 at the New York
Cotton Exchange. The exchange's existing contract covers just American
cotton.
