<HEADLINE>
FT  23 SEP 92 / UK Company News: Elswick rises 70% to Pounds 1.72m
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By WALTON MORAIS
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
ELSWICK, which sold its bicycle business last year to focus on print and
packaging, reported a 70 per cent rise in interim pre-tax profits to Pounds
1.72m and restored dividend payments.
The improvement reflected a 21 per cent increase in operating profit for the
six months to July 31 to Pounds 2.23m (Pounds 1.85m) and a 39 per cent
reduction in interest payment to Pounds 511,000 (Pounds 835,000).
Profits last time were depressed by losses of Pounds 465,000 from
discontinued businesses. The main one was Falcon Cycles, sold in December.
Sales of continuing businesses were up 5 per cent at Pounds 28.5 (Pounds
27.1m or Pounds 31.9m with discontinued businesses).
Mr Bill Cross, chairman, said the results reflected the resilience of its
core printing and packaging activities.
There is an interim dividend of 0.15p (0.22p). No final dividend was paid
last year. Earnings per share were 0.63p (0.41p).
</TEXT>
