<HEADLINE>
FT  23 SEP 92 / UK Company News: Wolstenholme Rink achieves 35% growth
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
PRE-TAX profits of Wolsten-holme Rink, the Lancashire-based metal powders
maker and supplier of products for the printing industry, showed a 35 per
cent improvement, from Pounds 1.24m to Pounds 1.68m, in the six months to
end-June.
Mr Tony Rink, joint chairman, said the advance had been achieved despite a
fall in turnover to Pounds 24.7m (Pounds 27.5m) and was mainly the result of
a recovery in the part of the business which supplies international printing
ink manufacturers. Profits had also been helped by the acquisition last year
of PCO, which had performed well, he added.
However, no improvement had been seen in trading conditions in the UK. Sales
in the printing supplies business had fallen and bad debts were still a
significant problem.
An improved interim dividend of 6.5p (6.3p) is declared, payable from
earnings of 14.4p (11.8p) per share.
