FT  23 SEP 92 / UK Company News: Brixton Estate advances 7% to Pounds 13m
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
DESPITE THE depressed property market, Brixton Estate, the investment and
development company, turned in pre-tax profits ahead 7 per cent at Pounds
12.6m for the six months to June 30.
The bulk of the company's revenue comes from letting its properties; rental
income was up 9 per cent at Pounds 24.9m.
'The vacancy rate for the company's property portfolio remains at about 7
per cent, and in the City of London, which is probably the most difficult
area, I am pleased to report that all of our buildings are fully occupied,'
said Mr Harry Axton, chairman.
Earnings per share were up to 5.64p (5.2p) and the interim dividend is
increased to 3p (2.9p). Mr Axton plans to retire as chairman after next
year's annual meeting. He is succeeded by Mr Douglas Gardner.
